messages.message: Hey team, I'm seeing some inconsistencies between what's being extracted in a build project vs. what the accuracy tests show as extracted value. These are some examples of values that the accuracy tests consistently extract inconsistently, while the build project extracts correctly with fairly high confidence (80+%). Happy to provide more details in the thread

Accuracy test from here (https://aihub.instabase.com/hub/apps/f461411e-48b1-4375-87f1-f783f39d6b00/accuracy/287)
Build project here (https://aihub.instabase.com/build/0192df4b-a579-7c4c-b44e-269911905f84)

I'm OOO tomorrow but can provide more details if necessary next week!

for ILDL1.pdf, maybe the ground truth values for `Legal Name Middle` and `Legal Name Suffix` should be “None”?

i ran your app and also got `None` for those fields on ILDL1.pdf

the good news is that i can reproduce all of the field values for the 3 docs in your screenshots in my app run

the bad news is still that they’re not consistent with Build :sweat_smile:

you could be running into this issue (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-2900)

here’s how to verify:
• create a new project using an existing project schema (see screenshot)
• select “CT AML KYC POC”
• you should see an empty project with your copied schema
• upload these 3 docs into the new project
• see whether you get the results from the app run / accuracy test
